# CHANGE.log 2026-06-04 (v2.2.0)

- **Streaming passthrough (new `stream` option):** pipe the upstream body
  straight to the client without buffering — for Server-Sent Events, NDJSON,
  and LLM token streaming. Additive and fully backward compatible (unset/`false`
  keeps the existing buffered JSON behavior).
	- `stream: true` always pipes; `stream: "auto"` pipes only when the upstream
	  `Content-Type` essence is stream-like (`text/event-stream`,
	  `application/x-ndjson`, `application/stream+json`, `application/octet-stream`);
	  `stream: (req) => boolean | "auto"` decides per request.
	- Security: all guards (auth, CSRF, CORS, rate limit, `validate`, SSRF) run
	  before the fetch, so streaming never bypasses them. Only `content-type` and
	  `cache-control` are forwarded; every other upstream header (including
	  `Set-Cookie`) is dropped. Adds `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, and
	  `X-Accel-Buffering: no` for `text/event-stream`.
	- `transformResponse` is skipped for streamed bodies; `monitor` is called
	  without the response; `log` fires a `response` event with `payload: "[stream]"`.
	- `"auto"` matches the parsed MIME essence exactly (not a loose substring),
	  so a stream-like charset on a non-stream type cannot trip the heuristic.
	- `timeoutMs` only guards time-to-headers; an in-progress stream has no idle
	  or total timeout (documented).
	- Added 13 streaming tests including guard-before-stream, SSRF-block,
	  header-stripping, and non-ok passthrough. `tsc` clean and 67/67 tests pass.

